611My sweet Frederic.
.an 2
----------
1. Brief von Julie Gundert, der an obigen Brief angeklebt ist.

.fo +
A few days ago I had much joy in receiving your precious letters of Janu-
ary. Your presents gave you much joy; for which I am glad it is right to
feel thankful to friends who do so much for you; but to see above all that
you think of the 2very1 great Gift God made to the world in giving his only
son that through 2Him1 we might have life. This is indeed the unspeakable
present we are to consider and accept with joy.

That you go on in your lessons well and are obedient is to me the sign that
God is with you and helps you, is it not? You pray to Him and you see His
answers! Yes believe Jesus loves you very much!

This week I am alone Papa and Marie have gone to Tellicherry and Cannanore,
I had just a letter from Marie who is wondering to recognise nothing at all
of the place she was born in. Dear Papa has not been very well of late.

Give a kiss to the dear brothers whose letters I was very glad to get. Love
and thanks to dear Miss Culman her kind letter has refreshed us about you.
.fo -
                                       Your Mama J. Gundert
